Session 4 is very important for CCEE because CDAC loves Wireshark display filters, packet-analysis logic, and iptables real-world use cases (Port Forwarding + Fail2ban).

Below are 30 MCQs (10 Basic + 10 Intermediate + 10 Advanced), tightly mapped to Session 4 theory + Lab 7, with exam-style traps.

Network Defense & Countermeasures ‚Äì Session 4
BASIC MCQs (1‚Äì10)
1. Wireshark is primarily used for:
A. Vulnerability scanning
B. Packet capturing and analysis
C. Firewall configuration
D. Intrusion prevention

2. Wireshark captures packets using which underlying library on Linux?
A. libnet
B. libpcap
C. tcpdump
D. netstat

3. Which Wireshark filter is used to display only TCP packets?
A. tcp==true
B. proto tcp
C. tcp
D. filter tcp

4. Display filters in Wireshark are applied:
A. Before packet capture
B. After packet capture
C. During packet transmission
D. At kernel level

5. Which protocol is most commonly analyzed for web traffic in Wireshark?
A. FTP
B. SMTP
C. HTTP/HTTPS
D. SNMP

6. Which Wireshark column shows packet arrival time?
A. Length
B. Protocol
C. Time
D. Info

7. A packet capture (.pcap) file stores:
A. Firewall rules
B. Packet headers and payloads
C. System logs only
D. Encrypted traffic only

8. Which tool can also capture packets from CLI similar to Wireshark?
A. Nessus
B. tcpdump
C. OpenVAS
D. iptables

9. Port forwarding in iptables is mainly implemented using which table?
A. filter
B. mangle
C. nat
D. raw

10. Fail2ban is mainly used to:
A. Forward packets
B. Detect malware
C. Block brute-force attacks
D. Capture packets

INTERMEDIATE MCQs (11‚Äì20)
11. Which Wireshark display filter shows packets from a specific IP?
A. ip=192.168.1.1
B. ip.addr == 192.168.1.1
C. src.ip = 192.168.1.1
D. addr.ip == 192.168.1.1

12. Capture filters in Wireshark are based on:
A. Wireshark syntax
B. tcpdump/libpcap syntax
C. iptables syntax
D. BPF notations only

13. Which filter displays only DNS queries?
A. dns
B. udp.port == 53
C. Both A and B
D. tcp.port == 53

14. While examining packet captures, repeated SYN packets without ACK indicate:
A. Normal traffic
B. Port scan or SYN flood
C. DNS query
D. HTTPS handshake

15. Which iptables chain is used for destination NAT (port forwarding)?
A. INPUT
B. OUTPUT
C. PREROUTING
D. POSTROUTING

16. In Wireshark, which field helps identify failed TCP connections?
A. TTL
B. TCP Flags
C. Window Size
D. MAC address

17. Fail2ban primarily relies on:
A. Packet inspection
B. Log file analysis
C. IDS signatures
D. Antivirus definitions

18. Which Wireshark filter shows only failed TCP connection attempts?
A. tcp.flags.syn == 1
B. tcp.flags.reset == 1
C. tcp.flags.syn == 1 && tcp.flags.ack == 0
D. tcp.flags.fin == 1

19. Real-world packet analysis is mainly useful for:
A. Increasing bandwidth
B. Detecting anomalies and attacks
C. Installing firewall rules
D. Updating antivirus

20. Which protocol is commonly abused in brute-force login attempts observed via Wireshark?
A. ICMP
B. SSH
C. ARP
D. SNMP

ADVANCED MCQs (21‚Äì30)
21. Which Wireshark filter is MOST suitable to detect SSH brute-force attempts?
A. tcp.port == 22
B. ip.addr == server_ip
C. tcp.flags.syn == 1
D. tcp.analysis.retransmission

22. During packet analysis, excessive RST packets usually indicate:
A. Normal termination
B. Network congestion
C. Scanning or failed connections
D. Encryption failure

23. Port forwarding using iptables exposes risk mainly because:
A. It increases bandwidth
B. It exposes internal services externally
C. It blocks internal traffic
D. It disables NAT

24. Fail2ban improves security by acting as a:
A. Proxy firewall
B. IDS only
C. Log-based intrusion prevention tool
D. Packet sniffer

25. In Wireshark, ‚ÄúFollow TCP Stream‚Äù is used to:
A. Capture packets
B. Reconstruct session data
C. Apply capture filters
D. Generate firewall rules

26. A sudden spike in DNS queries from a single host may indicate:
A. Normal browsing
B. DNS amplification attack
C. Brute-force attack
D. ARP poisoning

27. Which iptables rule is CRITICAL when using Fail2ban?
A. ACCEPT all traffic
B. Allow loopback traffic
C. Enable DROP/REJECT dynamically
D. Disable NAT

28. From CCEE perspective, Wireshark is best classified as:
A. Preventive security tool
B. Detective security tool
C. Corrective security tool
D. Deterrent control

29. Which Wireshark statistic helps identify top talkers?
A. IO Graphs
B. Conversations
C. Protocol Hierarchy
D. Endpoints

30. Which statement best aligns with CDAC exam philosophy?
A. Wireshark prevents attacks
B. Packet capture replaces firewall
C. Analysis tools support incident response
D. Fail2ban eliminates need for IDS

ANSWER KEY
Basic:
1-B, 2-B, 3-C, 4-B, 5-C, 6-C, 7-B, 8-B, 9-C, 10-C

Intermediate:
11-B, 12-B, 13-C, 14-B, 15-C, 16-B, 17-B, 18-C, 19-B, 20-B

Advanced:
21-A, 22-C, 23-B, 24-C, 25-B, 26-B, 27-C, 28-B, 29-D, 30-C

